        "unit": "W",
        "description": "Typical range for industrial laser cleaning of reflective metals like Dysprosium at 1064 nm to ablate contaminants without substrate melting (melting point ~1412°C). Starting at 200 W balances efficiency and safety; higher risks thermal damage due to moderate thermal conductivity (~10.7 W/m·K). Source: General Nd:YAG laser specs from IPG Photonics and studies on rare earth metal processing (e.g., J. Appl. Phys. on lanthanide ablation)."
